<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Holla1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Holla,</orth> interj. used 1) to call to a person to come near: <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.900" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 900</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.1.93" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 1, 93</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.4.66" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.109" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 109</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 18</bibl>. Joined to <cit><quote>ho:</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 1, 12</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to make to stop: <cit><quote>his flattering h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 284" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 284</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>cry h. to thy tongue,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.257" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 257</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>h., stand there!</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.2.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 2, 56</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) to express surprise: <cit><quote>h., what storm is this?</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.1.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 1, 25</bibl></cit> (Qq <emph>hollo</emph>). <cit><quote>h. h., that eye that told you so looked but a-squint,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.72" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 72</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>